  "texts": [
    "In NetVLAD, different features are assigned to different clustering centres.",
    "In conv-attention, different queries are assigned to different keys.",
    "In other words, the key can be regarded as the centre of the cluster, and assuming there are N keys, the distribution of the query's difference at N keys is computed to get the attention matrix (the difference is the attention).",
    "The major function of the attention mechanism is to filter the information.",
    "Our conv-attention classifies queries into keys (clustering centres), then the distribution of classifications is the filtering of queries (information).As shown in Fig. 2, we replace one of the self-attention layers with conv-attention, which is similar to the NetVLAD layer, both in the form of a single branch, while retaining the generation of the value (V) vector."
